{"title":"Aberration","url":"https://nethackwiki.com/wiki/Aberration","type":"markdown","data":"The **aberration** is a [monster class](/wiki/Monster_class \"Monster class\") that appears in [xNetHack](/wiki/XNetHack \"XNetHack\"). Aberrations are represented by the uppercase [U](/wiki/U \"U\") glyph (U), and are designated internally by the macro **S\\_ABERRATION**.\n\nThe aberration class \"replaces\" the [umber hulk](/wiki/Umber_hulk_\\(monster_class\\) \"Umber hulk (monster class)\") monster class from vanilla *[NetHack](/wiki/NetHack \"NetHack\")*, which has the titular monster as its only member, and includes several other existing monsters that are moved to the monster class.\n\nAberrations consist of the following monsters:\n\n- U [umber hulk](/wiki/Umber_hulk \"Umber hulk\")\n- U [mind flayer](/wiki/Mind_flayer \"Mind flayer\") (formerly h)\n- U [master mind flayer](/wiki/Master_mind_flayer \"Master mind flayer\") (formerly h)\n- U [quantum mechanic](/wiki/Quantum_mechanic \"Quantum mechanic\") (formerly Q)\n- U [genetic engineer](/wiki/Genetic_engineer \"Genetic engineer\") (formerly Q)\n\n## Strategy\n\nThe presence of mind flayers in the monster class serves primarily to avert the [YASD](/wiki/YASD \"YASD\") potential from using a blessed [scroll of genocide](/wiki/Scroll_of_genocide \"Scroll of genocide\") on them as a [dwarven](/wiki/Dwarf_\\(starting_race\\) \"Dwarf (starting race)\") player. This change additionally solves the problem of \"[minesflayers](/wiki/Minesflayer \"Minesflayer\")\", which occur in vanilla *NetHack* as a result of initial level creation for [Gnomish Mines](/wiki/Gnomish_Mines \"Gnomish Mines\") floors outside of [Minetown](/wiki/Minetown \"Minetown\") and [Mines' End](/wiki/Mines%27_End \"Mines' End\"): [mkclass](/wiki/Mkclass \"Mkclass\") may ignore out-of-depth rules when placing a random [humanoid](/wiki/Humanoid_\\(monster_class\\) \"Humanoid (monster class)\") monster.\n\n- *This page is a **[stub](/wiki/Category:Stubs \"Category:Stubs\")**. Should you wish to do so, you can contribute by [**expanding this page**.](https://nethackwiki.com/index.php?title=Aberration\\&action=edit)*\n","html":"<!DOCTYPE html>\n<html class=\"client-nojs\" lang=\"en\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<head>\n<meta charset=\"UTF-8\"/>\n<title>Aberration - NetHack Wiki</title>\n<script>document.documentElement.className = document.documentElement.className.replace( /(^|\\s)client-nojs(\\s|$)/, \"$1client-js$2\" );</script>\n<script>(window.RLQ=window.RLQ||[]).push(function(){mw.config.set({\"wgCanonicalNamespace\":\"\",\"wgCanonicalSpecialPageName\":false,\"wgNamespaceNumber\":0,\"wgPageName\":\"Aberration\",\"wgTitle\":\"Aberration\",\"wgCurRevisionId\":159430,\"wgRevisionId\":159430,\"wgArticleId\":37854,\"wgIsArticle\":true,\"wgIsRedirect\":false,\"wgAction\":\"view\",\"wgUserName\":null,\"wgUserGroups\":[\"*\"],\"wgCategories\":[\"Stubs\",\"XNetHack monster classes\"],\"wgBreakFrames\":false,\"wgPageContentLanguage\":\"en\",\"wgPageContentModel\":\"wikitext\",\"wgSeparatorTransformTable\":[\"\",\"\"],\"wgDigitTransformTable\":[\"\",\"\"],\"wgDefaultDateFormat\":\"dmy\",\"wgMonthNames\":[\"\",\"January\",\"February\",\"March\",\"April\",\"May\",\"June\",\"July\",\"August\",\"September\",\"October\",\"November\",\"December\"],\"wgMonthNamesShort\":[\"\",\"Jan\",\"Feb\",\"Mar\",\"Apr\",\"May\",\"Jun\",\"Jul\",\"Aug\",\"Sep\",\"Oct\",\"Nov\",\"Dec\"],\"wgRelevantPageName\":\"Aberration\",\"wgRelevantArticleId\":37854,\"wgRequestId\":\"2c3f740acb71c671712be273\",\"wgCSPNonce\":false,\"wgIsProbablyEditable\":false,\"wgRelevantPageIsProbablyEditable\":false,\"wgRestrictionEdit\":[],\"wgRestrictionMove\":[],\"wgWikiEditorEnabledModules\":[],\"wgCategoryTreePageCategoryOptions\":\"{\\\"mode\\\":0,\\\"hideprefix\\\":20,\\\"showcount\\\":true,\\\"namespaces\\\":false}\"});mw.loader.state({\"site.styles\":\"ready\",\"noscript\":\"ready\",\"user.styles\":\"ready\",\"user\":\"ready\",\"user.options\":\"ready\",\"user.tokens\":\"loading\",\"mediawiki.legacy.shared\":\"ready\",\"mediawiki.legacy.commonPrint\":\"ready\",\"mediawiki.skinning.interface\":\"ready\",\"skins.vector.styles\":\"ready\"});mw.loader.implement(\"user.tokens@0tffind\",function($,jQuery,require,module){/*@nomin*/mw.user.tokens.set({\"editToken\":\"+\\\\\",\"patrolToken\":\"+\\\\\",\"watchToken\":\"+\\\\\",\"csrfToken\":\"+\\\\\"});\n});RLPAGEMODULES=[\"site\",\"mediawiki.page.startup\",\"mediawiki.user\",\"mediawiki.page.ready\",\"mediawiki.searchSuggest\",\"skins.vector.js\"];mw.loader.load(RLPAGEMODULES);});</script>\n<link rel=\"stylesheet\" href=\"/load.php?debug=false&amp;lang=en&amp;modules=mediawiki.legacy.commonPrint%2Cshared%7Cmediawiki.skinning.interface%7Cskins.vector.styles&amp;only=styles&amp;skin=vector\"/>\n<script async=\"\" src=\"/load.php?debug=false&amp;lang=en&amp;modules=startup&amp;only=scripts&amp;skin=vector\"></script>\n<meta name=\"ResourceLoaderDynamicStyles\" content=\"\"/>\n<link rel=\"stylesheet\" href=\"/load.php?debug=false&amp;lang=en&amp;modules=site.styles&amp;only=styles&amp;skin=vector\"/>\n<meta name=\"generator\" content=\"MediaWiki 1.32.5\"/>\n<link rel=\"image_src\" href=\"/images/6/65/Nethackwiki-logo.png\"/>\n<link rel=\"shortcut icon\" href=\"/images/6/64/Favicon.ico\"/>\n<link rel=\"search\" type=\"application/opensearchdescription+xml\" href=\"/opensearch_desc.php\" title=\"NetHackWiki\"/>\n<link rel=\"EditURI\" type=\"application/rsd+xml\" href=\"https://nethackwiki.com/api.php?action=rsd\"/>\n<link rel=\"canonical\" href=\"/wiki/Aberration\"/>\n<!--[if lt IE 9]><script src=\"/load.php?debug=false&amp;lang=en&amp;modules=html5shiv&amp;only=scripts&amp;skin=vector&amp;sync=1\"></script><![endif]-->\n</head>\n<body class=\"mediawiki ltr sitedir-ltr mw-hide-empty-elt ns-0 ns-subject page-Aberration rootpage-Aberration skin-vector action-view\">\t\t<div id=\"mw-page-base\" class=\"noprint\"></div>\n\t\t<div id=\"mw-head-base\" class=\"noprint\"></div>\n\t\t<div id=\"content\" class=\"mw-body\" role=\"main\">\n\t\t\t<a id=\"top\"></a>\n\t\t\t<div class=\"mw-indicators mw-body-content\">\n</div>\n<h1 id=\"firstHeading\" class=\"firstHeading\" lang=\"en\">Aberration</h1>\t\t\t<div id=\"bodyContent\" class=\"mw-body-content\">\n\t\t\t\t<div id=\"siteSub\" class=\"noprint\">From NetHackWiki</div>\t\t\t\t<div id=\"contentSub\"></div>\n\t\t\t\t<div id=\"jump-to-nav\"></div>\t\t\t\t<a class=\"mw-jump-link\" href=\"#mw-head\">Jump to navigation</a>\n\t\t\t\t<a class=\"mw-jump-link\" href=\"#p-search\">Jump to search</a>\n\t\t\t\t<div id=\"mw-content-text\" lang=\"en\" dir=\"ltr\" class=\"mw-content-ltr\"><div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><p>The <b>aberration</b> is a <a href=\"/wiki/Monster_class\" title=\"Monster class\">monster class</a> that appears in <a href=\"/wiki/XNetHack\" title=\"XNetHack\">xNetHack</a>. Aberrations are represented by the uppercase <a href=\"/wiki/U\" title=\"U\">U</a> glyph (<span class=\"nhsym clr-white\">U</span>), and are designated internally by the macro <b>S_ABERRATION</b>.\n</p><p>The aberration class \"replaces\" the <a href=\"/wiki/Umber_hulk_(monster_class)\" title=\"Umber hulk (monster class)\">umber hulk</a> monster class from vanilla <i><a href=\"/wiki/NetHack\" title=\"NetHack\">NetHack</a></i>, which has the titular monster as its only member, and includes several other existing monsters that are moved to the monster class.\n</p><p>Aberrations consist of the following monsters:\n</p>\n<ul><li><span class=\"nhsym clr-brown\">U</span>&#160;<a href=\"/wiki/Umber_hulk\" title=\"Umber hulk\">umber hulk</a></li>\n<li><span class=\"nhsym clr-magenta\">U</span> <a href=\"/wiki/Mind_flayer\" title=\"Mind flayer\">mind flayer</a> (formerly <span class=\"nhsym clr-magenta\">h</span>)</li>\n<li><span class=\"nhsym clr-brightmagenta\">U</span> <a href=\"/wiki/Master_mind_flayer\" title=\"Master mind flayer\">master mind flayer</a> (formerly <span class=\"nhsym clr-magenta\">h</span>)</li>\n<li><span class=\"nhsym clr-cyan\">U</span> <a href=\"/wiki/Quantum_mechanic\" title=\"Quantum mechanic\">quantum mechanic</a> (formerly <span class=\"nhsym clr-cyan\">Q</span>)</li>\n<li><span class=\"nhsym clr-green\">U</span> <a href=\"/wiki/Genetic_engineer\" title=\"Genetic engineer\">genetic engineer</a> (formerly <span class=\"nhsym clr-green\">Q</span>)</li></ul>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Strategy\">Strategy</span></h2>\n<p>The presence of mind flayers in the monster class serves primarily to avert the <a href=\"/wiki/YASD\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"YASD\">YASD</a> potential from using a blessed <a href=\"/wiki/Scroll_of_genocide\" title=\"Scroll of genocide\">scroll of genocide</a> on them as a <a href=\"/wiki/Dwarf_(starting_race)\" title=\"Dwarf (starting race)\">dwarven</a> player. This change additionally solves the problem of \"<a href=\"/wiki/Minesflayer\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Minesflayer\">minesflayers</a>\", which occur in vanilla <i>NetHack</i> as a result of initial level creation for <a href=\"/wiki/Gnomish_Mines\" title=\"Gnomish Mines\">Gnomish Mines</a> floors outside of <a href=\"/wiki/Minetown\" title=\"Minetown\">Minetown</a> and <a href=\"/wiki/Mines%27_End\" title=\"Mines&#39; End\">Mines' End</a>: <a href=\"/wiki/Mkclass\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Mkclass\">mkclass</a> may ignore out-of-depth rules when placing a random <a href=\"/wiki/Humanoid_(monster_class)\" title=\"Humanoid (monster class)\">humanoid</a> monster.\n</p>\n<div class=\"stub\">\n<dl><dd><i>This page is a <b><a href=\"/wiki/Category:Stubs\" title=\"Category:Stubs\">stub</a></b>. Should you wish to do so, you can contribute by <a class=\"external text\" href=\"https://nethackwiki.com/index.php?title=Aberration&amp;action=edit\"><b>expanding this page</b>.</a></i></dd></dl>\n</div>\n\n<!-- \nNewPP limit report\nCached time: 20240926182205\nCache expiry: 604800\nDynamic content: false\nCPU time usage: 0.031 seconds\nReal time usage: 0.462 seconds\nPreprocessor visited node coun