ed by the uppercase [[U]] glyph ({{white|U}}), and are designated internally by the macro '''S_ABERRATION'''.\n\nThe aberration class \"replaces\" the [[Umber hulk (monster class)|umber hulk]] monster class from vanilla ''[[NetHack]]'', which has the titular monster as its only member, and includes several other existing monsters that are moved to the monster class.\n\nAberrations consist of the following monsters:\n\n* {{monsymlink|umber hulk}}\n* {{magenta|U}} [[mind flayer]] (formerly {{monsym|mind flayer}})\n* {{brightmagenta|U}} [[master mind flayer]] (formerly {{monsym|master mind flayer}})\n* {{cyan|U}} [[quantum mechanic]] (formerly {{monsym|quantum mechanic}})\n* {{green|U}} [[genetic engineer]] (formerly {{monsym|genetic engineer}})\n\n==Strategy==\nThe presence of mind flayers in the monster class serves primarily to avert the [[YASD]] potential from using a blessed [[scroll of genocide]] on them as a [[Dwarf (starting race)|dwarven]] player. This change additionally solves the problem of \"[[minesflayer]]s\", which occur in vanilla ''NetHack'' as a result of initial level creation for [[Gnomish Mines]] floors outside of [[Minetown]] and [[Mines' End]]: [[mkclass]] may ignore out-of-depth rules when placing a random [[Humanoid (monster class)|humanoid]] monster.\n{{stub}}<!--{{variant-37x}}-->\n[[Category:xNetHack monster classes]]"}